  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The _XX_tt_CC_rr_ee_aa_tt_ee_PP_oo_pp_uu_pp_SS_hh_ee_ll_ll(3X11R5) function ensures that the specified class
    is a subclass of Shell and, rather than using insert_child to attach the
    widget to the parent's children list, attaches the shell to the parent's
    pop-ups list directly.

    A spring-loaded pop-up invoked from a translation table already must exist
    at the time that the translation is invoked, so the translation manager
    can find the shell by name. Pop-ups invoked in other ways can be created
    ``on-the-fly'' when the pop-up actually is needed. This delayed creation
    of the shell is particularly useful when you pop up an unspecified number
    of pop-ups. You can look to see if an appropriate unused shell (that is,
    not currently popped up) exists and create a new shell if needed.

